1. Feature Name: Rule-Based Email Filtering
Description: This feature allows users to set up rules to automatically filter incoming emails into specific folders, enhancing email organization and efficiency.
Key Functionality: Users can create rules based on specific criteria such as sender, subject line, or keyword to manage incoming emails effectively.
User Benefit: This feature saves time and improves productivity by automatically sorting emails into designated folders, reducing manual effort.

2. Feature Name: Email Prioritization Rules
Description: This feature enables users to prioritize certain emails over others by setting up rules to categorize them accordingly, ensuring important emails are easily identified.
Key Functionality: Users can define rules to categorize emails based on importance criteria, ensuring critical messages are promptly addressed.
User Benefit: Users can focus on important emails first, leading to better time management and improved responsiveness.

3. Feature Name: Automated Email Forwarding and Copying
Description: This feature provides users with the option to automatically forward or copy emails to specific recipients based on predefined rules, streamlining communication processes.
Key Functionality: Users can set up rules to automatically forward or copy emails to designated recipients, ensuring timely sharing of information.
User Benefit: This feature simplifies information sharing and collaboration by automating the process of forwarding or copying relevant emails.

4. Feature Name: Rule Management Interface
Description: This feature offers users the ability to easily edit, delete, or disable existing rules in the email rules engine, providing flexibility and control over email management.
Key Functionality: Users can conveniently manage their email rules by editing, deleting, or disabling rules as needed, optimizing email organization.
User Benefit: This feature empowers users to customize their email rules according to changing needs, enhancing efficiency and customization options.

