## Workflow Step: User Story 4: As a user, I want to be able to view and search through all incoming emails in one unified inbox in the Email Router platform.
Based on the user story provided, a potential feature for the Email Router platform could be:

Unified Inbox Feature:

Description:
Allow users to view and search through all incoming emails in one unified inbox.

User Stories:
- As a user, I want to access a single inbox that consolidates all incoming emails from multiple sources.
- As a user, I want to be able to search for specific emails across all accounts in the unified inbox.
- As a user, I want to have a seamless experience when navigating through emails from different sources in one place.

## Workflow Step: Feature: Unified Inbox
Grouping similar user stories related to managing emails, messages, notifications, etc. into a cohesive feature called Unified Inbox. This feature allows users to access and manage all their communications from different sources in a single, centralized location for better organization and convenience.

## Workflow Step: Task: Create a unified inbox displaying all incoming emails with search functionality
To create a unified inbox with search functionality for incoming emails, some potential features could include:

1. Unified Inbox: Enable users to view all incoming emails from multiple accounts in one centralized inbox.
2. Search Functionality: Implement a search bar allowing users to search for specific emails based on keywords, sender, or other criteria.
3. Filtering Options: Provide filtering options to help users sort and prioritize emails according to different parameters such as date, sender, or attachments.
4. Notifications: Implement email notifications to alert users of new incoming emails in real-time.
5. Customization: Allow users to customize their inbox settings, such as email sorting preferences, email preview options, and notification settings.
6. Sorting Capabilities: Enable users to sort emails based on categories like unread, flagged, or important to easily manage their inbox.
7. Quick Actions: Include options for users to perform quick actions on emails, such as archive, delete, mark as read, or move to folders.
8. Integration: Integrate with other productivity tools or email services to enhance functionality and streamline workflow for users.

By organizing similar user stories into cohesive groups, these features can be further refined and prioritized to create a seamless and user-friendly unified inbox with search functionality for incoming emails.

## Workflow Step: User Story 5: As a user, I want to be able to categorize and label incoming emails for better organization.
Based on the user story provided, a potential feature for the product could be "Email categorization and labeling functionality."

## Workflow Step: Feature: Email Categorization
Categorize emails into folders based on predefined rules and user-defined criteria to help users organize and manage their emails more efficiently. This feature would involve grouping user stories related to sorting, filtering, and organizing emails, leading to a more cohesive and user-friendly email management system.

## Workflow Step: Task: Develop feature to categorize and label emails based on user-defined criteria
Feature Name: Email Categorization and Labeling
Description: This feature enables users to organize and categorize their emails effectively based on user-defined criteria.

Key Functionality:
1. Rule Creation: Users can create custom rules to automatically categorize incoming emails into specific folders or labels.
2. Labeling Options: Users have the flexibility to assign color-coded labels to emails based on keywords, sender information, or other specified criteria.
3. Automated Categorization: Implement automated algorithms that categorize incoming emails according to predefined rules or user-defined settings.

User Benefit: By utilizing this feature, users can efficiently manage their email inbox, save time on manual sorting, and ensure important emails are prioritized and easily accessible. It enhances organization and productivity in handling email communications.

## Workflow Step: User Story 6: As a user, I want to be able to create rules to automatically process incoming emails based on certain conditions.
Feature: Email Rules Automation

Description: This feature allows users to create rules for automatically processing incoming emails based on specific conditions. Users can define rules such as moving emails to specific folders, marking them as important, deleting them, or forwarding them to another email address. This feature enhances productivity by reducing manual effort in organizing and managing emails.

## Workflow Step: Feature: Email Rules Engine
1. Feature Name: Rule-Based Email Filtering
Description: This feature allows users to set up rules to automatically filter incoming emails into specific folders, enhancing email organization and efficiency.
Key Functionality: Users can create rules based on specific criteria such as sender, subject line, or keyword to manage incoming emails effectively.
User Benefit: This feature saves time and improves productivity by automatically sorting emails into designated folders, reducing manual effort.

2. Feature Name: Email Prioritization Rules
Description: This feature enables users to prioritize certain emails over others by setting up rules to categorize them accordingly, ensuring important emails are easily identified.
Key Functionality: Users can define rules to categorize emails based on importance criteria, ensuring critical messages are promptly addressed.
User Benefit: Users can focus on important emails first, leading to better time management and improved responsiveness.

3. Feature Name: Automated Email Forwarding and Copying
Description: This feature provides users with the option to automatically forward or copy emails to specific recipients based on predefined rules, streamlining communication processes.
Key Functionality: Users can set up rules to automatically forward or copy emails to designated recipients, ensuring timely sharing of information.
User Benefit: This feature simplifies information sharing and collaboration by automating the process of forwarding or copying relevant emails.

4. Feature Name: Rule Management Interface
Description: This feature offers users the ability to easily edit, delete, or disable existing rules in the email rules engine, providing flexibility and control over email management.
Key Functionality: Users can conveniently manage their email rules by editing, deleting, or disabling rules as needed, optimizing email organization.
User Benefit: This feature empowers users to customize their email rules according to changing needs, enhancing efficiency and customization options.

## Workflow Step: Task: Implement rule creation and processing functionality for automated email handling
To implement rule creation and processing functionality for automated email handling, you can define the following features based on organizing similar user stories into cohesive groups:

1. Rule Creation:
- Interface for users to create new rules based on specific criteria such as sender, subject, keywords, etc.
- Wizard or guided process to help users set up conditions and actions for each rule.
- Support for creating multiple rules to organize and handle emails effectively.
- Ability to prioritize rules to ensure emails are processed in the desired order.

2. Rule Processing:
- Automated scanning of incoming emails to match against created rules.
- Efficient processing of emails based on rule criteria, such as routing to folders, marking as important, forwarding, etc.
- Logging and reporting functionalities to track the application of rules on incoming emails.
- Error handling mechanisms to address cases where rules cannot be applied successfully.
- Option to manually trigger rule processing for specific emails or folders.

By organizing similar user stories into cohesive groups, these features can help in creating a comprehensive and user-friendly rule creation and processing functionality for automated email handling.

