## Workflow Step: Feature: Email Composition
1. Feature Name: Compose New Email
   Description: This feature allows users to create and send a new email message.
   Key Functionality: Enables users to start a new email composition from scratch.
   User Benefit: Streamlines the process of creating and sending new emails efficiently.

2. Feature Name: Reply to Email
   Description: This feature enables users to respond to received email messages.
   Key Functionality: Provides users with the ability to reply directly to the sender of an email.
   User Benefit: Facilitates quick and easy communication by allowing users to respond promptly to incoming emails.

3. Feature Name: Forward Email
   Description: This feature allows users to forward received email messages to other recipients.
   Key Functionality: Enables users to share email content with additional recipients.
   User Benefit: Simplifies the process of sharing important information or messages with others.

4. Feature Name: Attach Files to Email
   Description: This feature enables users to include attachments, such as documents or images, in their email messages.
   Key Functionality: Allows users to upload and attach files to their emails for sharing.
   User Benefit: Enhances communication by enabling users to share relevant files and information easily.

5. Feature Name: Format Text in Email
   Description: This feature provides users with formatting options for text in email messages.
   Key Functionality: Allows users to customize the appearance of text, such as font style, size, and color.
   User Benefit: Helps users create visually appealing and organized email messages.

6. Feature Name: Add Recipients to Email
   Description: This feature enables users to add multiple recipients to an email message.
   Key Functionality: Allows users to include multiple email addresses in the recipient field.
   User Benefit: Facilitates communication with multiple recipients in a single email message.

7. Feature Name: Save Email Drafts
   Description: This feature allows users to save unfinished email messages as drafts for later completion.
   Key Functionality: Enables users to store incomplete emails and resume editing at a later time.
   User Benefit: Prevents loss of work and allows users to work on emails at their convenience.

8. Feature Name: Add Signature to Email
   Description: This feature enables users to include a personalized signature at the end of their email messages.
   Key Functionality: Allows users to create and add a custom signature to their outgoing emails.
   User Benefit: Adds a professional touch to emails and helps users establish their identity or branding.

## Workflow Step: Task: Integrate email composition and reply functionality within the platform
To define features for integrating email composition and reply functionality within the platform, we need to organize similar user stories into cohesive groups. Here are some key features based on this approach:

1. **Email Composition Feature Group:**
   - Create new emails within the platform
   - Add recipients, subject, and body to compose emails
   - Attach files or documents to emails
   - Save draft emails for later completion
   - Format text and add images to emails

2. **Email Reply Feature Group:**
   - Reply to incoming emails directly within the platform
   - Reply all or forward emails to multiple recipients
   - Access email history and previous conversations
   - Include original message in replies
   - Mark emails as read, unread, or flag important messages

By organizing similar user stories into these cohesive groups, we can ensure the email composition and reply functionality within the platform meets the needs of users effectively.

